plugin for object spread
npm install --save-dev babel-plugin-transform-object-rest-spread

date manipulation
sudo yarn add moment react-dates

sudo yarn add react-redux for {connect} <Provider />

## about git remote setting
git remote -v // show git remotes
git remote set-url <remote-name: like origin> <remote-url>
e.g. git remote set-url origin git@github.com:mandoo180/myapp.git

you can check the config file at .git/config

ls -a ~/.ssh

sudo yarn add mini-css-extract-plugin >> to extract css file from css and scss files

git add .
git commit -m "first commit"  >> git commit -am "first commit" >> add + commit
git remote add <github-url>
git push -u origin master

heroku create <app-name>
git push heroku master ....build....
heroku open
heroku logs...

before deploy the app, need to setup webpack and package.json....

regular dependencies vs development dependencies
sudo yarn add chalk --dev
sudo yarn install --production >> install only regular dependencies
sudo yarn install >> install all

